B040C001V001	40	1	1	A roll of the birth of Jesus Christ, son of David, son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham fathered Isaac, and Isaac fathered Jacob, and Jacob fathered Judah and his brethren,
B040C001V003	40	1	3	and Judah fathered Pharez and Zarah of Tamar, and Pharez fathered Hezron, and Hezron fathered Ram,
B040C001V004	40	1	4	and Ram fathered Amminadab, and Amminadab fathered Nahshon, and Nahshon fathered Salmon,
B040C001V005	40	1	5	and Salmon fathered Boaz of Rahab, and Boaz fathered Obed of Ruth, and Obed fathered Jesse,
B040C001V006	40	1	6	and Jesse fathered David the king. And David the king fathered Solomon, of her 
B040C001V007	40	1	7	and Solomon fathered Rehoboam, and Rehoboam fathered Abijah, and Abijah fathered Asa,
B040C001V008	40	1	8	and Asa fathered Jehoshaphat, and Jehoshaphat fathered Joram, and Joram fathered Uzziah,
B040C001V009	40	1	9	and Uzziah fathered Jotham, and Jotham fathered Ahaz, and Ahaz fathered Hezekiah,
B040C001V010	40	1	10	and Hezekiah fathered Manasseh, and Manasseh fathered Amon, and Amon fathered Josiah,
B040C001V011	40	1	11	and Josiah fathered Jeconiah and his brethren, at the Babylonian removal.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after the Babylonian removal, Jeconiah fathered Shealtiel, and Shealtiel fathered Zerubbabel,
B040C001V013	40	1	13	and Zerubbabel fathered Abiud, and Abiud fathered Eliakim, and Eliakim fathered Azor,
B040C001V014	40	1	14	and Azor fathered Sadok, and Sadok fathered Achim, and Achim fathered Eliud,
B040C001V015	40	1	15	and Eliud fathered Eleazar, and Eleazar fathered Matthan, and Matthan fathered Jacob,
B040C001V016	40	1	16	and Jacob fathered Joseph, the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is named Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	All the generations, therefore, from Abraham unto David 
B040C001V018	40	1	18	And of Jesus Christ, the birth was thus: For his mother Mary having been betrothed to Joseph, before their coming together she was found to have conceived from the Holy Spirit,
B040C001V019	40	1	19	and Joseph her husband being righteous, and not willing to make her an example, did wish privately to send her away.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	And on his thinking of these things, lo, a messenger of the Lord in a dream appeared to him, saying, 'Joseph, son of David, you may not fear to receive Mary your wife, for that which in her was conceived 
B040C001V021	40	1	21	and she shall bring forth a son, and you shall call his name Jesus, for he shall save his people from their sins.'
B040C001V022	40	1	22	And all this has come to pass, that it may be fulfilled that was spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	'Lo, the virgin shall conceive, and she shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel,' which is, being interpreted 'With us 
B040C001V024	40	1	24	And Joseph, having risen from the sleep, did as the messenger of the Lord directed him, and received his wife,
B040C001V025	40	1	25	and did not know her till she brought forth her son -- the first-born, and he called his name Jesus.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	And Jesus having been born in Beth-Lehem of Judea, in the days of Herod the king, lo, mages from the east came to Jerusalem,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	saying, 'Where is he who was born king of the Jews? For we saw his star in the east, and we came to bow to him.'
B040C002V003	40	2	3	And Herod the king having heard, was stirred, and all Jerusalem with him,
B040C002V004	40	2	4	and having gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people, he was inquiring from them where the Christ is born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	And they said to him, 'In Beth-Lehem of Judea, for thus it has been written through the prophet,
B040C002V006	40	2	6	And you, Beth-Lehem, the land of Judah, you are by no means the least among the leaders of Judah, for out of you shall come one leading, who shall feed My people Israel.'
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod, privately having called the mages, did inquire exactly from them the time of the appearing star,
B040C002V008	40	2	8	and having sent them to Beth-Lehem, he said, 'Having gone -- inquire you exactly for the child, and whenever you may have found, bring me back word, that I also having come may bow to him.'
B040C002V009	40	2	9	And they, having heard the king, departed, and lo, the star, that they did see in the east, did go before them, till, having come, it stood over where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	And having seen the star, they rejoiced with exceeding great joy,
B040C002V011	40	2	11	and having come to the house, they found the child with Mary his mother, and having fallen down they bowed to him, and having opened their treasures, they presented to him gifts, gold, and frankincense, and myrrh,
B040C002V012	40	2	12	and having been divinely warned in a dream not to turn back unto Herod, through another way they withdrew to their own region.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	And on their having withdrawn, lo, a messenger of the Lord does appear in a dream to Joseph, saying, 'Having risen, take the child and his mother, and flee to Egypt, and be you there till I may speak to you, for Herod is about to seek the child to destroy him.'
B040C002V014	40	2	14	And he, having risen, took the child and his mother by night, and withdrew to Egypt,
B040C002V015	40	2	15	and he was there till the death of Herod, that it might be fulfilled that was spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying, 'Out of Egypt I did call My Son.'
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod, having seen that he was deceived by the mages, was very enraged, and having sent forth, he murdered all the male children in Beth-Lehem, and in all its borders, from two years and under, according to the time that he inquired exactly from the mages.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremiah the prophet, saying,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	'A voice in Ramah was heard -- lamentation and weeping and much mourning -- Rachel weeping 
B040C002V019	40	2	19	And Herod having died, lo, a messenger of the Lord in a dream does appear to Joseph in Egypt,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	saying, 'Having risen, take the child and his mother, and be going to the land of Israel, for they have died -- those seeking the life of the child.'
B040C002V021	40	2	21	And he, having risen, took the child and his mother, and came to the land of Israel,
B040C002V022	40	2	22	and having heard that Archelaus does reign over Judea instead of Herod his father, he was afraid to go there, and having been divinely warned in a dream, he withdrew to the parts of Galilee,
B040C002V023	40	2	23	and coming, he dwelt in a city named Nazareth, that it might be fulfilled that was spoken through the prophets, that 'A Nazarene he shall be called.'
B040C003V001	40	3	1	And in those days comes John the Baptist, proclaiming in the wilderness of Judea,
B040C003V002	40	3	2	and saying, 'Reform, for come near has the reign of the heavens,'
B040C003V003	40	3	3	for this is he who was spoken of by Isaiah the prophet, saying, 'A voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare you the way of the Lord, straight make you His paths.'
B040C003V004	40	3	4	And this John had his clothing of camel's hair, and a girdle of skin round his loins, and his nourishment was locusts and honey of the field.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then were going forth unto him Jerusalem, and all Judea, and all the region round about the Jordan,
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and they were baptized in the Jordan by him, confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	And having seen many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming about his baptism, he said to them, 'Brood of vipers! Who did show you to flee from the coming wrath?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Bear, therefore, fruits worthy of the reformation,
B040C003V009	40	3	9	and do not think to say in yourselves, A father we have -- Abraham, for I say to you, that God is able out of these stones to raise children to Abraham,
B040C003V010	40	3	10	and now also, the axe unto the root of the trees is laid, every tree therefore not bearing good fruit is hewn down, and to fire is cast.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	'I indeed do baptize you with water to reformation, but he who after me is coming is mightier than I, of whom I am not worthy to bear the sandals, he shall baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire,
B040C003V012	40	3	12	whose fan 
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then comes Jesus from Galilee upon the Jordan, unto John to be baptized by him,
B040C003V014	40	3	14	but John was forbidding him, saying, 'I have need by you to be baptized -- and you do come unto me!'
B040C003V015	40	3	15	But Jesus answering said to him, 
B040C003V016	40	3	16	And having been baptized, Jesus went up immediately from the water, and lo, opened to him were the heavens, and he saw the Spirit of God descending as a dove, and coming upon him,
B040C003V017	40	3	17	and lo, a voice out of the heavens, saying, 'This is My Son -- the Beloved, in whom I did delight.'
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then Jesus was led up to the wilderness by the Spirit, to be tempted by the Devil,
B040C004V002	40	4	2	and having fasted forty days and forty nights, afterwards he did hunger.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	And the Tempter having come to him said, 'If Son you are of God -- speak that these stones may become loaves.'
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But he answering said, 
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then does the Devil take him to the 
B040C004V006	40	4	6	and said to him, 'If Son you are of God -- cast yourself down, for it has been written, that, His messengers He shall charge concerning you, and on hands they shall bear you up, that you may not dash on a stone your foot.'
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jesus said to him again, 
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again does the Devil take him to a very high mount, and does show to him all the kingdoms of the world and the glory of them,
B040C004V009	40	4	9	and said to him, 'All these to you I will give, if falling down you may bow to me.'
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then said Jesus to him, 
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then does the Devil leave him, and lo, messengers came and were ministering to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	And Jesus having heard that John was delivered up, did withdraw to Galilee,
B040C004V013	40	4	13	and having left Nazareth, having come, he dwelt at Capernaum that is by the sea, in the borders of Zebulun and Naphtalim,
B040C004V014	40	4	14	that it might be fulfilled that was spoken through Isaiah the prophet, saying,
B040C004V015	40	4	15	'Land of Zebulun and land of Naphtali, way of the sea, beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the nations! --
B040C004V016	40	4	16	The people that is sitting in darkness saw a great light, and to those sitting in a region and shadow of death -- light arose to them.'
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time began Jesus to proclaim and to say, 
B040C004V018	40	4	18	And Jesus, walking by the sea of Galilee, saw two brothers, Simon named Peter and Andrew his brother, casting a drag into the sea -- for they were fishers --
B040C004V019	40	4	19	and he said to them, 
B040C004V020	40	4	20	and they, immediately, having left the nets, did follow him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	And having advanced from there, he saw other two brothers, James of Zebedee, and John his brother, in the boat with Zebedee their father, refitting their nets, and he called them,
B040C004V022	40	4	22	and they, immediately, having left the boat and their father, did follow him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	And Jesus was going about all Galilee teaching in their synagogues, and proclaiming the good news of the reign, and healing every disease, and every malady among the people,
B040C004V024	40	4	24	and his fame went forth to all Syria, and they brought to him all having ailments, pressed with manifold sicknesses and pains, and demoniacs, and lunatics, and paralytics, and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And there followed him many multitudes from Galilee, and Decapolis, and Jerusalem, and Judea, and beyond the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	And having seen the multitudes, he went up to the mount, and he having sat down, his disciples came to him,
B040C005V002	40	5	2	and having opened his mouth, he was teaching them, saying:
